                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 816 48/12</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-14T18:00:00-05:56">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>All night downpour drove home anew to thousands who slept in the open the real
                    need for shelter, no doubt if marines or warships have extra tents Department
                    will rush same here. Three earthquakes of unusual severity during night rendered
                    situation more disagreeable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
